1) cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the estimation of mm-Wave MIMO channels, which is a problem related to information theory. 
2) cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a novel scheme to estimate the channel vector by exploiting spatio-temporal correlation and sparse scattering, which is a signal processing problem. 
3) cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the estimation of channels for mm-Wave communication, which is a multimedia application. 
4) cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the estimation of channels for wireless communication, which is a networking problem. 
5) cs.SP (Speech Processing): The paper deals with the estimation of channels for communication, which is a speech processing problem.
